section: compiler
synopsis: Unpack strict enumeration fields by default with -O
description:
  The new flag ``-funbox-strict-enums``, enabled by default at ``-O`` and
  higher, unpacks strict constructor fields whose type is an enumeration
  (all constructors nullary), such as ``Bool``. Such a field is stored as
  its constructor tag in a ``Word8#``, ``Word16#`` or ``Word#`` instead of
  a pointer, making the constructor smaller. This builds on the branchless
  enumeration unpacking introduced for ``{-# UNPACK #-}`` (#26970).
issues: #605 #26970
